    "This approach updates all weights of the model, theoretically allowing for maximal adaptation.",
    "A large-scale empirical study on 37 LLMs [124] found that models fine-tuned via FFT significantly outperformed other methods in assertion generation and test evolution tasks.",
    "Similarly, A3Test [5] and AthenaTest [135] also employed FFT, demonstrating its effectiveness.Parameter-efficient Fine-tuning (PEFT).",
    "To overcome the high computational and storage costs of FFT, PEFT methods like LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) have emerged.",
    "These methods freeze the majority of the model's parameters and adjust only a small subset."
